# Cloudflare Pages redirects / rewrites
# Syntax: <from>  <to>  <status>
# Reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Order matters - Cloudflare matches the first rule. Static files (assets,
# /install, _shell.html, etc.) take precedence over these rules; this file
# only governs routes that don't match a real file.

# SPA fallback. Most routes are prerendered to their own /route/index.html and
# those static files are served directly (and take precedence over this rule).
# This catch-all covers the SPA client-router entry: the home route and any
# route without a prerendered file (e.g. the runtime /s/$owner/$gistId gist
# shares) get the SPA shell (copied to index.html at build time) with a 200,
# and the hydrated client router renders the matching route + prefetches links.
#
# Target is /index.html, NOT /_shell.html: Cloudflare Pages auto-redirects any
# *.html URL to its extensionless form (308), so a `/_shell.html` rewrite
# target gets bounced to /_shell and the /* rule re-matches -> infinite 308
# loop. index.html is served as the directory index without that redirect.

# Studio SPA (its own client router, base /studio/, staged into public/studio
# by scripts/stage-studio.ts). Real assets under /studio/assets/* are served
# directly (static precedence); deep client routes (/studio/sessions, ...) fall
# through to the studio shell. This MUST precede the site-wide /* catch-all,
# else /studio/<route> would render the marketing SPA -> blank "Invariant failed".
/studio/*  /studio/index.html  200
/*  /index.html  200
